(numRXQEntries, power_pad).explanation: RXQ entries are internal memory structures that do not directly affect the power consumption of I/O pads, which handle external signal interfacing;

(numRXQEntries, power_switching).explanation: Increasing the number of RXQ entries requires more transistors and memory cells that switch states during operation, directly increasing switching power consumption;

(numRXQEntries, time).explanation: The number of RXQ entries affects performance metrics like throughput but does not directly determine execution time, which depends on workload and other architectural factors;
